    <section id="products">
      <h2>4. Products &amp; Services</h2>
      <p><strong>Descriptions:</strong> HVAC (heating, ventilation, air conditioning), plumbing, and refrigeration services — a home-services / light-commercial contractor. The mix of residential vs. commercial work, install vs. repair, and the refrigeration sub-segment is not disclosed.</p>
      <p><strong>Pricing model:</strong> Not disclosed. Contractors here typically blend time-and-materials service calls, fixed-fee installations, and — in better businesses — recurring maintenance agreements. The mix is unknown and is the biggest swing factor for revenue quality.</p>
      <p><strong>Differentiators:</strong> The listing emphasizes profitability and included land/real estate. Owned real estate removes lease risk and carries standalone value — but the listing does not separate real-estate value from going-concern value, so the ~6.0x multiple may conflate an operating business with a real-estate asset.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="market">
      <h2>5. Market Analysis</h2>
      <p><strong>Industry size and trends:</strong> HVAC and plumbing services are large, fragmented, non-discretionary home-services markets driven by housing stock, replacement cycles, and electrification / heat-pump conversion (in Canada, cold-climate heat-pump incentive programs). Refrigeration adds a light-commercial dimension. The sector is a popular consolidation target for private equity in both the US and Canada.</p>
      <p><strong>Drivers and barriers:</strong> Drivers — equipment replacement, energy-efficiency rebates, new construction, recurring maintenance contracts. Barriers — skilled-tradesperson labor shortage, seasonality, housing-market and interest-rate cyclicality, equipment cost inflation.</p>
      <p><strong>Peer benchmarks:</strong> Lower-middle-market HVAC/plumbing contractors in North America commonly transact at ~3x–6x SDE/EBITDA, with the high end reserved for businesses with recurring service-agreement revenue, a real management layer, and clean multi-year growth. A ~$327K-SDE business with an undisclosed contract mix would typically sit at the <strong>lower</strong> end; the ~6.0x ask here is at the top of the band and bundles unpriced real estate.</p>
    </section>

